This paper is primarily focused on the networking aspect of mobile crowdsensing, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of game theory to analyze user behavior, which falls under the category of theoretical computer science (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper proposes a data sharing market, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures for efficient data processing and storage, falling under the categories of distributed computing (cs.DC), social and information networks (cs.SI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
